tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
I'm Ch Bharathi 40yrs old  visited Dr Manjunath Reddy.for my health problems as I'm suffering with chronic low back ache along with right tennis elbow since past few months...as I have been to Dr Manjunath Reddy. he has diagnosed all the two'conditions what I m suffering with..and gave me proper treatment for my condition and now I'm doing well with my health.. the injection and the medication given by the doctor are very effective and the speed of recovery was very fast then the expectation time.. the experience within the clinical primises was good along with the staff in the clinic are good.. the staff work and the work of staff was good I liked the way they treated the patient.each and every one in that clinic are good and respectful towards the patient.
And I strongly recommend Dr Manjunath Reddy.
The patience of Dr Manjunath Reddy was soo excellent without any hesitation.
Thank you Dr Manjunath Reddy sir for your time and the medication given by you and your treatment.
I recommend Dr Manjunath Reddy for orthopaedic problems.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
Iam sai  kumar has visited Dr majuathReddy sir in the month june as I have been suffering with neck pain along with cervical spondylosis since fewmonths as I am software employe sue lockdown my schedule is work from home ..... as I have explained all my problems with doctor ..... I liked the way he explained whole problem why I was facing .......I likes the way doctor spent his time with me for explaining the prolemwith out any irration..and he answers all my questions very politely and clearly as a friend..
And more over I have visited about 2 hospitals previously before visiting Dr majuathReddy Reddy sir....previous experience was very bad as they could not diagnose properly....and now I am fully satisfied  with the teatment given by Dr manjunath reddy  sir....
And finally i strongly belive that sirs treatemt was fentabuls and even I strongly recommend Dr g manjunath reddy for good and excellent orthopedic treatment.
Tq sir ....
And I'm back to my normal position with out any so of pain at all since few days..

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review: This is sravanthi posa had visited dr Manjunath reddy few months before as I meet with an accident got fracture to my right wrist previously when I was meet with an accident visted the other doctor immediately but they could not diagnose properly …And after few days I visted dr Manjunath reddy  then doctors recommended for X-ray then there was a fractur in my wrist joint then doctor suggested pop for few weeks. The fracture got heeled after few weeks then doctor recommended for physiotherapy i even took physio treatment for few days.now my fracture got healed properly with out any problem. Even my wrist got twisted inwards could not hold anything properly but now after the treatment given by doctor my wirst and my fracture got healed properly.I thank doctor Manjunath reddy sir for his wonderful treatment.and I strongly recommend him for any orthopaedic problems.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review: I had taken my mother for an elbow fracture. Firstly the doctor was downright arrogant and refused to take her appt.My mom is a dementia patient , 78 yrs.finally he did the plastering *** *** **** * ****** *** **** she was bleeding the next day under her arm. I took her back to get the plaster trimmed and he asked his assistant to do the trimming *** *** *** ********** *After 4 weeks I took my mother to another Ortho for a checkup.** **** *** ********** *** **** **** ***** *** *** *** ** ***** ** *** ***** *** ** ***** **** *******.her hand was swollen due to the ulcer.there was a hole on her arm *** ** *** ***** **** *********** he charged me 12k for it.I request ppl NOT TO go to  THIS GUY. hes not only arrogant, rude, insensitive *** ** ****** ** **** *** **** ***** *** now she has an ulcer plus the fracture.
reply_text: Hi friends I was expecting this verymuch. First point I was leaving for emergency surgery and she came for op. Inspite of that I considered to see her because she is a elderly lady. Second I diagnosed properly the fracture and I gave options to her. I totally refused to put plaster because the patient skin is fragile. She came back after two days to me and insisted to put plaster. I warned her about this problem. Basically this lady leave her mother to caretakers. This is what happens. Basically the patient needs proper care. That is lacking here. Last thing about money we have discounted her charges. Don’t believe these type of badmouthing about us. They want to show all their personal frustrations on us. Finally whatever it is I wish her speedy recovery. Thank you
